
GENERAL INFORMATION

    This is GNUtrition, a recipe and food nutritional analysis
    application for the GNU Operating System.

    GNUtrition can be found on the main GNU FTP server:
            http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/gnutrition (via HTTP)
            ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/gnutrition (via FTP)
    
    It can also be found on the GNU mirrors; please use a mirror if
    possible.  The FTP mirror list is available at
    http://www.gnu.org/order/ftp.html.
    http://ftpmirror.gnu.org/gnutrition/ will automatically redirect
    to a nearby mirror.

    The official web site is:

            http://www.gnu.org/software/gnutrition

    This is alpha software that is currently being ported to Python 3
    from Python 2.  Any help with finishing this process will be
    greatly appreciated!  For more information about how you can help,
    visit https://www.gnu.org/software/gnutrition/py3.html


